Project Overview:
This project investigates the classification of European Union banking systems using unsupervised learning techniques.
Different clustering approaches were applied and compared to identify groups of countries with similar banking sector characteristics and to determine the most significant factors influencing cluster formation.

Tools:
- MATLAB
- Statistics and Machine Learning Toolbox
- Fuzzy Logic Toolbox
- Neural Clustering Tool

Methods Applied:
- Data Normalization
- K-Means Clustering
- Fuzzy C-Means Clustering
- Neural Network Clustering
- Cluster Profile Analysis
- Comparative Cluster Evaluation

Project Workflow:
1. Data preparation and normalization.
2. Clustering using K-Means for different numbers of clusters.
3. Clustering using Fuzzy C-Means.
4. Identification of representative countries within each cluster.
5. Neural clustering analysis.
6. Comparison of clustering results and interpretation of cluster profiles.

Results:
The project compares several clustering techniques and demonstrates how different approaches reveal structural similarities and differences among European banking systems.
